parameters.MEDIUM: deionized water containing 50 mM DMPO, 0.001 mM FeSO4 and 0.01 mM H2O2

parameters.REMARKS: A 10g/L stock dispersion was prepared by dispersing NM powder  in MQ water. Then a 100 mg/L NM dispersion in 1 mM NaNO3  prepared by adding 200 uL of NM stock dispersion in the NaNO3 solution. Dispersion (20 mL in a 50 mL centifuge PP tube) was sonicate 15  min in a sonication bath (120 W nominal). Then the dispersion was titrated from the respective pH 6-7 to basic (11) pH by adding NaOH and let the system stabilized for 20 min between each acid addition (each ELS measurement)

A 10g/L stock dispersion was prepared by dispersing NM powder  in 1 mM NaOH. Then a 100 mg/L NM dispersion in 1 mM NaNO3 at pH 11 was prepared by adding 200 uL of NM stock dispersion in the NaNO3 basic (NaOH) solution. Dispersion (20 mL in a 50 mL centifuge PP tube) was sonicate 15  min in a sonication bath (120 W nominal). Then the dispersion was titrated from basic (11) to acidic (3) pH by adding HNO3 and let the system stabilized for 20 min between each acid addition (each ELS measurement)

protocol.endpoint: NFA screeing mass of organic coating

parameters.SAMPLE_FOLDER: The sample holder is a 3M Color Laser Transparency Film plate covered with a homogenous adhesive layer (0.25 mm) of Acronal® V 215
parameters.T.SAMPLE_PREPARATION: Spread a thin layer of powder on the sticky sample holder pressing the surface with a spatula. A nitrogen (or compressed air) gun is used to gently blow the NM residuals not attached to the plate's surface.
